3	//! `SYS_EXIT` — terminate a target process and free its slot.
4	//!
5	//! PM's kill and exit paths end here: once PM decides a process is done —
6	//! signal disposition terminate, or a voluntary `PM_EXIT` — it issues
7	//! `SYS_EXIT` on the target, exactly MINIX 3's `pm_exit → sys_clear →
8	//! clear_proc` shape (`kernel/system/do_clear.c`). Slice 4.6 completes the
9	//! 4.5 "exit-lite" into full teardown, in MINIX's order:
10	//!
11	//! - cancel the target's `SYS_SETALARM` timer (a stale `EARLIEST_ALARM`
12	//!   cached minimum is harmless — the next gated scan finds no due alarm);
13	//! - set `RTS_PROC_STOP` (dequeues via `rts_set` if the target was runnable);
14	//! - if it was blocked `SENDING`, unlink it from the destination's `caller_q`
15	//!   so a terminated proc's queued message is never delivered;
16	//! - wake every process blocked on the dead endpoint with `EDEADSRCDST`
17	//!   (MINIX `clear_ipc_refs`): senders queued on the dead proc's `caller_q`
18	//!   and receivers waiting on it specifically both resume with the error in
19	//!   `x0`, and a dedicated-priv proc's pending-notification bits are purged;
20	//! - tear down the address space: free every leaf frame ([`walk_leaves`]),
21	//!   invalidate the ASID's TLB entries, free the page-table tree
22	//!   ([`AddrSpace::destroy`]), and recycle the ASID;
23	//! - free the slot: bump the endpoint generation (so every stale endpoint
24	//!   now fails `okendpt` with `EDEADSRCDST`), zero the signal/IPC/timer
25	//!   state, and store `RTS_SLOT_FREE` for `SYS_FORK` to reuse.
26	//!
27	//! `SELF` (and the caller's own endpoint) are rejected: full teardown of the
28	//! *active* address space mid-kernel-call would pull the TTBR0 out from under
29	//! the running caller. PM — the sole intended holder — always names a third
30	//! party. MINIX's self-exit arm (`SIGABRT` for system procs) has no consumer
31	//! here yet.
